<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese And Japanese Ministerial Trade Talks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 9 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese Minister of Foreign
Trade and Economic Cooperation, Wu Yi, meeting today with Shinji
Sato, the Japanese Minister of International Trade and Industry,
said that China wants to work with Japan to increase the trade
volume to 100 billion US dollars by the end of the century.
</P>
<P>
She said that the two sides should treasure their hard-won
accomplishments in bilateral trade and economic cooperation in 25
years since their relations were normalized.
</P>
<P>
Two-way trade between China and Japan was worth more than 60
billion US dollars in 1996. Wu said she hopes the two countries
will strengthen exchanges between their governments and their
people.
</P>
<P>
Sato said that further promotion of bilateral trade and
economic cooperation will help promote prosperity and development
in both countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
