<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 1600 GMT, June 9 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA -- Singaporean Prime Minister Goh Chok Tong arrived here
Monday for a two-day visit to the Philippines.
</P>
<P>
BAGHDAD -- Iraq has taken measures to resume trade ties with
Syria by buying Syrian food and re-opening customs offices on the
border with Syria, according to the Iraqi News Agency (INA).
</P>
<P>
ANKARA -- President of the Republic of Bosnia-Herzegovina Alija
Izetbegovic said here Monday that peace would never be implemented
fully unless war crimes ended.
</P>
<P>
ANKARA -- Iranian Deputy Foreign Minister Alaeddin Bourujerdi
arrived here Monday on a surprise visit to Turkey, carrying a
message from Iranian President Hashemi Rafsanjani concerning ties
between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
LAGOS -- Officials of the Nigerian government insisted on
Sunday night that the coup soldiers in Sierra Leone would be
dislodged from power "by other means" if negotiations failed, the
"Guardian" reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG -- South Africa Monday called on those involved in
fighting in the Congo capital of Brazzaville to agree to ceasefire
with immediate effect.
</P>
<P>
CAIRO -- Egyptian President Hosni Mubarak said Monday that the
Palestinians and Israelis held "promising" talks here Sunday on
the resumption of deadlocked peace negotiations. 
</P>
