<HEADLINE> China Beats Indonesia 4-2 in World Junior Soccer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, June 9 (Xinhua) -- China beat defending champion
Indonesia 4-2 in an Asian zone final game of the world junior
soccer championship here on Monday.
</P>
<P>
After the victory, China has qualified for the next round with
two wins. Yesterday, the Chinese team beat Japan 1-0 in the same
group.
</P>
<P>
Seven nations from China, Japan, Indonesia, Malaysia, the
Philippines, South Korea and Singapore are competing in the
tournament, which started last Saturday. The semifinal will be
played on Wednesday, and the final is on Thursday. 
</P>
