<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EU, Japan to Hold Summit Meeting on June 25 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, June 9 (Xinhua) -- The European Union(EU) and Japan
will hold their sixth annual summit meeting in The Hague, the
Netherlands, on June 25, an European Commission spokesman
announced on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Japanese Prime Minister Ryutaro Hashimoto will come to the
Dutch city to meet the current President of the European Council,
Dutch Prime Minister Wim Kok and the President of the European
Commission Jacques Santer.
</P>
<P>
"They will amongst others exchange views on recent developments
in the EU and Japan, their bilateral relations, developments in
the world trading system, and other relevant international
issues," the spokesman told reporters.
</P>
<P>
He said that the Japanese Foreign Minister Yukihido Ikeda, his
Ducth counterpart Hans van Mierlo, and the Vice-President of the
European Commission Sir Leon Brittan would also attend the
upcoming Summit.
</P>
<P>
In the Declaration of the The Hague signed in 1991, the EU and
Japan agreed to further intensify political and economic relations
and to meet annually at the highest level.  
</P>
</TEXT>
