<HEADLINE> Cabinet Reshuffed in Eritrea </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, June 9 (xinhua) -- The Eritrean national assembly
has approved the restructuring of government institutions and
ministerial posts proposed by President Isaias Afwerki, the
latest issue of the English weekly newspaper ''Eritrea Profile''
reported.
</P>
<P>
According to a new list of cabinet ministers published by the
newspaper, Haile Woldetensae, former Minister of Finance and
Development, will take the post of Minister of Foreign Affairs,
while former Foreign Minister Petros Solomon will be Minister of
Marine Resources, and Gebreselassie Yosef will be Minsiter of
Finance in the 17-member new cabinet.
</P>
<P>
Minister of Defence Sebhat Ephrem, Minister of Justice Fawzia
Hashim, Minister of Local Government Mohmoud Ahmed Sherifo and
others remain their posts in the new cabinet.
</P>
<P>
The Eritrean government was set up in June, 1993, one month
after its independence. The cabinet has been reshuffed in
November, 1995. 
</P>
</TEXT>
