<HEADLINE> UN Plane Detained by UNITA Returns to Launda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAUNDA, June 9 (Xinhua) -- The U.N. plane which was detained
by UNITA (the national union for the total independence of
Angola) last Saturday in the Angolan eastern city of Luau
returned to capital Launda this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
The plane sent by the United Nations Verification Mission in
Angola was detained by UNITA members in Luau while it was on its
mission to carry members of Non-governmetal organizations to
attend a meeting in Luena of Moxico Province.
</P>
<P>
The plane was released after the United Nations Verification
Mission made consultations with UNITA. 
