<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kuwait Strives to Realize Diversification in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, June 9 (Xinhua) -- A Kuwaiti minister stressed
today that Kuwaiti government's main objective at present is to
realize diversification in production so as to reduce imports.
</P>
<P>
Jassem Abdullah Al-Mudhaf, Kuwaiti minister of commerce and
industry made the remarks while inaugurating a two-day conference
on trade and industry which is aimed at finding ways for expanding
industry along with crude oil in the oil-rich Gulf state.
</P>
<P>
Representatives of 27 trade and industrial organizations are
taking part in the conference to jointly seek solutions to
problems facing industrial development in Kuwait.
</P>
<P>
Al-Mudhaf said Kuwait is now depending on oil as a main source
of revenue and most other public needs are imported.
</P>
<P>
He called for more investments into industrial sector,
particularly private undertakings.
</P>
<P>
He said Kuwait has formed a committee to draft a foreign
investment law which would surmount difficulties facing the
industrial and trade sectors and encourage direct and indirect
investment through incentives.
</P>
<P>
He said the Kuwaiti government has also started the process of
creating a free trade zone which would help expand trade and
industry. 
</P>
</TEXT>
