<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Xinhua On Patriotism (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 10 (Xinhua) -- China's Xinhua News Agency, in an
article entitled "Cultivating Patriotic Feelings and Encouraging
Dedication to the Motherland", says that with Hong Kong's return
to the motherland on July 1 growing near, the hearts of all
Chinese people are full of patriotic feelings.
</P>
<P>
It reports that a major project to educate people in patriotism
and to promote reforms, opening up and socialist development on
the eve of Hong Kong's return is the 100 Patriotic Education Bases
designated by the Propaganda Department of the Communist Party of
China (CPC) Central Committee.
</P>
<P>
"Providing an education in patriotism is a cause that can
improve the overall quality of the whole nation and promote
socialist cultural and ethical progress," it says.
</P>
<P>
It quoted President Jiang Zemin as saying, "education in
patriotism is an important part of cultural and ethical progress,
and increased patriotic education should run through the whole of
the socialist modernization drive."
</P>
<P>
To give a patriotic education to more people, the Propaganda
Department of the CPC Central Committee has selected 100 patriotic
movies, 100 types of patriotic books, and the 100 Education Bases
of Patriotism.
</P>
<P>
These bases demonstrate China's splendid 5,000 years of
civilization, painting a grand picture of the Chinese people's
unremitting efforts in building the country.
</P>
<P>
They consist of four groups:
</P>
<P>
The first group is cultural relics sites, which tell the story
of how the nation's ancestors suffered many hardships to build
Chinese civilization, contributing to the progress of human
civilization.
</P>
<P>
The second is museums and memorials to the Chinese nation's
struggle against foreign invaders to defend the freedom, dignity
and sovereignty of the nation.
</P>
<P>
The third is memorials and sites which show the revolutionary
deeds of the Chinese people and the Chinese Communist Party in
modern times, telling people that only socialism can save China.
</P>
<P>
The fourth tells the stories of model workers and model
construction projects in the People's Republic of China, which was
founded in 1949, showing that only socialism can develop China,
and only the reforms and opening-up can make China prosperous and
strong.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
