<HEADLINE> Forum on Reforming State-Owned Enterprises Held in beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 10 (Xinhua) -- A forum on "Deepening Reforms and
Revitalizing State-Owned Enterprises" was held by the Propaganda
Department of the Communist Party of China Central Committee and
the State Economic and Trade Commission (SETC) today in Beijing to
discuss this urgent and difficult problem in China's economy.
</P>
<P>
It is also a popular topic with the press. The participants in
the forum said they agree that extensive media coverage of ten
successful state-owned enterprises sponsored by the Propaganda
Department and the SETC earlier this year have had a good effect.
</P>
<P>
The experience of the ten enterprises shows that state-owned
enterprises can be revitalized by market competition, they say,
pointing out that once state-owned enterprises decide to turn to
the market, their potential will become practical competitiveness.
</P>
<P>
They also spoke highly of the role the media has played in
pushing the reforms. The reforms have reached a critical stage,
and the participants urged governments at all levels to create
external conditions that are conducive to changing the methods of
operation of the state-owned enterprises.
</P>
<P>
They also called on the media to provide accurate reports of
the state-owned enterprises' experiences to help the reforms.
</P>
</TEXT>
