<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Elephants, Humans Compete for Resources in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, June 10 (Xinhua) -- The future of the elephants in
southern African countries, which include Zimbabwe, has been
linked to the growth of the human population.
</P>
<P>
According to a document circulated to delegates at the 10th
conference of Convention on International Trade in Endangered
Species (CITES) being held in Harare, humans competed with the
jumbo for the same resources, and elephant densities had an
inverse relationship with those of humans.
</P>
<P>
The Africa Resources Trust which prepared the document said
Malawi, South Africa and Zimbabwe were reaching the point where
land requirements by rural people could no longer be satisfied.
</P>
<P>
The future of elephants outside protected areas in the
southern Africa region was critically dependent on their
competitiveness in a land use context, said the Trust, a local
non-governmental organisation.
</P>
<P>
Current estimates of the elepnant population in southern
Africa stand at 187,239, with most of the animals found in
Botswana which has 71,586, Malawi 1,651, Namibia 8,901, South
Africa 10,010, Zambia 26,275 and Zimbabwe 67,971.
</P>
<P>
Latest data list the number of elephants inside protected
areas in Zimbabwe at 54,377, while 13,594 are outside.
</P>
<P>
Elephant densities were generally higher in protected areas
while survival of the jumbo outside these areas was highly
dependent on their value as a component of land use systems.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970610.0068 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Spain's Carlos Sainz Wins Acropolis Rally </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
ATHENS, June 10 (Xinhua) -- Carlos Sainz of Spain, driving a
Ford escort, won the 44 Acropolis rally, finishing 17
seconds ahead of Finland's Juha Kankunnen with a total time of 4
hours 56 minutes and 24 seconds on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Richard Burns of Britain was third, Tommi Makinen of Finland
fourth and Sweden's Thomas Radstrom finished fifth.
</P>
<P>
Carlos Sainz has won the world championship twice.
</P>
<P>
The three-day rally, which started on Sunday at the foot of the
Acropolis here, covered a total distance of 1,263 kilometres, which
included 20 special sections stretching 458 kilometres. 
</P>
</TEXT>
