<HEADLINE> Russian-Belarusian Union Treaty Comes Into Force </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, June 10 (Xinhua) -- The Russian-Belarusian Union
Treaty, and its accompanying charter, became effective in Belarus
today after Belarusian President Alexander Lukashenko signed them
on the ratification by the upper house of the Belarusian
parliament.
</P>
<P>
In Minsk, capital of Belarus, all 59 members of the Council of
the Republic (upper house) voiced their yes votes. The lower house
approved the treaty earlier.
</P>
<P>
The Russian Federation Council (upper house) today also
approved the treaty with 111 affirmative votes and three
abstentions, said Itar-Tass. But it has to yet to be signed by
Russian President Boris Yeltsin.
</P>
<P>
The treaty and charter conform with internationally accepted
standards and are in the interests of the two Slavic ex-Soviet
republics, said the Russian council. They layed a firm foundation
for strengthening political, economic and military cooperation
between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
The deal, signed by Yeltsin and Lukashenko, in Moscow in April
and on May 23, is designed for closer integration of the two
nations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
