<HEADLINE> China to Increase Cooperation with Macedonia: Premier </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 10 (Xinhua) -- Premier Li Peng praised Macedonian
President Kiro Gligorov's efforts at improving Sino-Macedonian
friendship and increasing bilateral ties during a meeting by the
two leaders in Beijing today.
</P>
<P>
Li said that China and Macedonia are traditional friends and
that bilateral relations have developed smoothly since the
establishment of diplomatic ties.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese Government attaches great importance to relations
with Macedonia, he said, and is ready to expand the cooperation
through joint efforts.
</P>
<P>
Gligorov said that there are no problems between China and
Macedonia and that the two are respected friends and have smooth
cooperation. China's great changes and remarkable economic
achievements are significant to bilateral relations, he said,
especially to economic and trade ties.
</P>
<P>
Praising China for respecting other countries' choices,
Gligorov said that Macedonia places importance on strengthening
exchanges with China.
</P>
<P>
Li said the Chinese Government is willing to expand economic
cooperation and trade with Macedonia on the basis of equality and
mutual benefits and said he hopes that the two governments will
act in keeping with market economy rules and international
practices, and help their enterprises cooperate on various levels
and through different channels.
</P>
<P>
China will encourage Chinese businessmen to establish joint
ventures and projects, provide buyer's credit and participate in
bidding on major projects in Macedonia, Li said, emphasizing that
the two governments should offer favorable conditions for
cooperation between companies.
</P>
<P>
Gligorov said Macedonia and China, after building a foundation
of good political relations, should adopt necessary measures to
make substantial progress in economic and trade cooperation.
</P>
<P>
