<HEADLINE> Algerian Government Resigns </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALGIERS, June 10 (Xinhua) -- Algerian Prime Minister Ahmed
Ouyahia today tendered the resignation of his government to
President Liamine Zeroual, Algeria Press Service reported.
</P>
<P>
Zeroual later held discussion with Ouyahia on the resignation
and commissioned him to run the government for the time being, the
agency added.
</P>
<P>
In the parliamentary elections held on June 5, Zeroual's
National Democratic Assembly comprising Ouyahia won 155 seats in
the new 380-seat parliament, the first multiparty parliament since
the beginning of a insurgency by extremists in 1992 in which more
than 60,000 people died.
</P>
<P>
According to reliable Algerian sources, Zeroual would likely
charge the resigning prime minister with forming a new government
in a few days.
</P>
<P>
The Algerian government headed by Ahmed Ouyahia was formed
in December, 1995. 
</P>
