<HEADLINE> Record Entry for Nagano Olympics </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVE, June 10 (Xinhua) -- A record 79 countries and regions
including Guinea-Bissau, the Virgin Islands and Ghana have
registered to take part in next year's Winter Olympics in Nagano,
Japan, the International Olympic Committee announced in Lausanne,
Switzerland, on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The 79 countries and regions all met the June 7 deadline for
accreditation, although competitors nominated by National Olympic
Committees will still have to meet qualification standards set by
the IOC in agreement with international winter sports federations.
</P>
<P>
The last Winter Olympics, in Lillehammer, Norway, in 1994,
attracted a total of 1,737 competitors from 67 countries.
</P>
<P>
The presence of 12 new federations and the addition to the
programme of women's ice hockey, curling and snowboarding is
expected to bring the number of competitors to close to 2,500 in
Nagano. 
</P>
</TEXT>
