<HEADLINE> Myanmar Leader Receives Malaysian FM </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, June 10 (Xinhua) -- Chairman of the Myanmar State Law
and Order Restoration Council Senior-General Than Shwe today
received visiting Malaysian Foreign Minister Abdullah Ahmad Badawi
who arrived here this morning, state-run TV Myanmar reported this
evening.
</P>
<P>
Abdullah, who is presently chairman of the Standing Committee
of the Association of Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN), is on a
mission to convey to the Myanmar leader the ASEAN decision that
Myanmar, along with Cambodia and Laos, will be admitted into the
grouping in July when the Association holds its 30th annual
ministerial meeting in Kuala Lumpur.
</P>
<P>
The decision to integrate the three countries into the regional
grouping was reached by ASEAN foreign ministers at their special
meeting held in the Malaysian capital on May 31.
</P>
<P>
Myanmar obtained observer status of the ASEAN at the
Association's 29th Annual Meeting of Foreign Ministers held in
Jakarta last July.
</P>
<P>
The Malaysian foreign minister has been to Myanmar for several
times and his last visit was in October 1996.
</P>
<P>
ASEAN now groups Brunei, Indonesia, Malaysia, Singapore, the
Philippines, Thailand and Vietnam.  
</P>
