<HEADLINE> China's Newest Municipality Chooses New Leaders </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, June 10 (Xinhua) -- Chongqing in southwest China,
which became the fourth municipality of China in March, chose its
new leaders at the first session of the Chongqing People's
Congress today.
</P>
<P>
Pu Haiqing was elected mayor, and seven vice-mayors were
elected.
</P>
<P>
Pu, 56, is a member of the Communist Party of China and has
served as vice-governor of Sichuan Province, standing committee
member of the Sichuan Provincial Party Committee, executive
vice-governor of Sichuan, and executive vice-secretary of the
Sichuan Provincial Party Committee.
</P>
<P>
Since September, 1996, he has been the executive vice-secretary
of the Sichuan Provincial Party Committee, vice-secretary of the
Chongqing Municipal Party Committee, acting mayor of Chongqing,
and secretary of the municipal party committee.
</P>
<P>
The leadership of the Municipal People's Congress was also
elected, with Wang Yunlong elected director of the congress's
standing committee.
</P>
<P>
