<HEADLINE> Ramos Orders Probe of Abuses Against Filipino Workers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, June 11 (Xinhua) -- Philippine President Fidel Ramos
today ordered the investigation of reports that at least two
Filipino women have been detained and raped by their employers in
the Commonwealth of Northern Mariana Islands (CNMI).
</P>
<P>
In a handwritten note, President Ramos ordered Foreign
Secretary Domingo Siazon and Labor Secretary Leonardo Quisumbing
to submit a report on their findings as soon as possible.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, two congressmen urged the government to immediately
revoke its labor agreement with CNMI, citing that US federal
authorities have documented at least two Filipino women detained
and raped by their employers in CNMI.
</P>
<P>
They also claimed that cases of abuses against Filipino workers
in CNMI have increased by 160 percent. From January to March this
year, the Philippine labor office in CNMI received 151 complaints
for labor violations from Filipino contracted workers.
</P>
<P>
There is a total of 25,000 Filipino migrant workers in CNMI, a
chain of islands in the Pacific Ocean.
</P>
<P>
Stories of abuses against Filipino overseas workers often hit
the headlines of local media, which reported that everyday there
are two Filipino overseas workers dying of abuses.
</P>
<P>
The Philippines has six million contracted workers in more than
100 countries and regions. 
</P>
</TEXT>
