<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Artist Liu Changchao Dies at 90 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANTOU, June 10 (Xinhua) -- Liu Changchao, a Chinese artist
best known for painting on bamboo with Chinese ink, died of
illness at the age of 90 today in Shantou city, south China's
Guangdong province.
</P>
<P>
Liu, born in 1907 in the city of Jieyang, developed a fondness
for painting as a boy. He had learned painting techniques from
renowned Chinese artists such as Sun Peigu, Huang Binhong, Pan
Tianshou and Zhu Wenyun.
</P>
<P>
Liu was skillful at painting mountains, rivers and flowers. His
bamboo painting was highly acclaimed both in China and overseas,
and his work has been exhibited in several countries and regions,
including the United States, France, Australia, Japan, Thailand,
and Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Liu entered the Shanghai School of Fine Arts in 1927. He was a
member of the Chinese Artists' Association. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
