<DOCNO> XIE19970610.0102 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Malaysia Airlines Launches Electronic Ticketing System </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, June 10 (Xinhua) -- Malaysia Airlines today
launched an electronic ticketing system, which marked the
beginning of a ticketless air travel era.
</P>
<P>
The system introduced by the airlines in cooperation with
Maybank will be convenient to air travelers and improve
efficiency.
</P>
<P>
Under the system, air travelers need only to go through three
simple steps -- first they phone the Malaysia Airlines ticket
office for booking their flights and get their transaction number,
then with that number they could effect payment for their seat
through their Automated Teller Machine (ATM) cards at Maybank ATM
machines in any part of the country, and with the receipt issued
by the ATM machine, they could proceed straight to the check-in
counter at the airport for their boarding pass.
</P>
<P>
However, this facility would only be available to domestic air
travelers in the country for the time being, according to the
airlines officials.
</P>
<P>
At a launching ceremony for the ticketing system, Malaysia
Airlines Chairman Tajudin Ramli said an electronic ticketing
system for international flight bookings would be introduced once
confirmation was received from the International Air Travel
Association.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
