<HEADLINE> Share Prices Fall Further on Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, June 10 (Xinhua) -- Share prices continued to
decline on the Singapore market as the benchmark Straits Times
Industrials fell by another 15.43 points to close at 2014.78
points today.
</P>
<P>
The total market volume increased to 124 million units, valued
at 313.22 million Singapore dollars (about 219.03 million US
dollars). Declines continued to lead advances by 200 to 113, while
310 other counters remained unchanged.
</P>
<P>
The Keppel Land warrant 00 was the most actively traded counter
as it registered a turnover of 13.08 million units. It was
followed by Datapulse which had 11.09 million shares traded. The
Hong Kong Land was next with 8.33 million of its shares changed
hands.
</P>
