<HEADLINE> Ramos Welcomes Admission of New Members to ASEAN </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, June 10 (Xinhua) -- Philippine President Fidel Ramos
today welcomed the forthcoming admission of Cambodia, Laos and
Myanmar into the Association of Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN).
</P>
<P>
The three new members will be formally admitted into ASEAN this
July despite the U.S. strong opposition against Myanmar's entry
into the body which groups Brunei, Indonesia, Malaysia, the
Philippines, Singapore, Thailand and Vietnam at present.
</P>
<P>
The expansion of ASEAN to encompass all ten nations in
Southeast Asia fulfills the vision of a regional group free from
animosities, divisions and barriers of the past, Ramos said.
</P>
<P>
"With an ASEAN Ten, we are in a better position to consolidate
understanding, solidarity and cooperation, as well as insure
steady progress for the members of the Southeast Asia family which
constitutes a vast market of 440 million people," he said.
</P>
<P>
Ramos added that the more economically-advanced ASEAN states
would now be able to assist the three countries within an ASEAN
framework.
</P>
<P>
"We will help them more capably and, within a shorter
time-frame, integrate themselves into our growing and increasingly
prosperous regional market in Southeast Asia," he said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
