<HEADLINE> Chinese Vice-President Meets Omani Sultan's Special Representative </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 10 (Xinhua) -- China and Oman should establish
long-term and stable cooperative relations, Vice-President Rong
Yiren said during talks here earlier today with Thuwainy Bin
Shihab Al-Said, a special representative of Oman's Sultan Qabus
Bin Said.
</P>
<P>
Saying that China treasures its friendship and cooperation with
Oman, Rong said the two countries should jointly explore new
cooperative paths which can meet the demand of the times and cater
to the conditions and development of the two countries. They
should also expand bilateral economic cooperation in economy,
trade, petroleum, metallurgy, agriculture, fishery and water
conservancy.
</P>
<P>
In his welcome to the Omani guest, Rong said that Thuwainy's
current visit to China is very important as it offers the
opportunity for various departments and business people of the two
sides to have extensive contacts and explore possibilities for
bilateral cooperation in various fields. These activities will
push forward the development of bilateral friendship and
cooperation, he noted.
</P>
<P>
Rong added that Oman, under the leadership of Sultan Qabus, has
made unceasing efforts to safeguard national independence, develop
the national economy and improve Omani people's lives, and has
been successful in doing so.
</P>
<P>
Oman has played a positive role in promoting the unity among
Arab states and working toward peace and stability in the Gulf
Region, added Rong.
</P>
<P>
Expressing his appreciation for the warm reception he received
during this visit, Thuwainy said that the sincere welcome has
revealed the depth of the friendship the Chinese government and
people have for the Omani government and people.
</P>
<P>
Thuwainy said that Oman, under the leadership of Sultan Qabus,
is concentrating on the country's economic development -- just as
China is doing.
</P>
<P>
He noted that his country places great emphasis on its ties
with China, hoping to further bilateral friendship and cooperation
in various fields including politics, economy and technology, and
wishing a greater success for the Chinese government and people in
their progress.
</P>
<P>
Thuwainy invited Rong to pay another visit to Oman, which Rong
said he appreciated.
</P>
<P>
Before the meeting, Rong presided over a welcoming ceremony for
Thuwainy, who is here as Rong's guest.
</P>
<P>
