<HEADLINE> Thailand Cuts Business Registration Time </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, June 10 (Xinhua) -- The Thai Commerce Ministry has
enforced a plan to speed up services for new businesses by cutting
the registration time to two hours from three days.
</P>
<P>
The move is part of the government's public sector efficiency
improvement program aimed at improving services of government
agencies, local newspapers said.
</P>
<P>
The measure will be in force first in Bangkok and then extended
to branches of the commercial registration department under the
ministry in other provinces.
</P>
<P>
The office of the Civil Service Commission Monday signed a pact
with a local rating agency to evaluate the performance of the
department based on three main aspects, that is, service coverage,
service quality and service efficiency.  
</P>
