<HEADLINE> Sino-Cuban Joint Economic, Trade Commission Meets in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 10 (Xinhua) -- The ninth session of Sino-Cuban
Joint Inter-Governmental Economic and Trade Commission was held
here today.
</P>
<P>
Wu Yi, Chinese minister of foreign trade and economic
cooperation, together with Ricardo Cabrisas Ruiz, the Cuban
minister of foreign trade, presided over the meeting, which is the
third time the two foreign trade ministers have co-sponsored the
meeting since 1994.
</P>
<P>
They exchanged views on issues of common concern in the
economic and trade field.
</P>
<P>
Extending a welcome to Cabrisas, Wu said China attaches great
importance to its cooperative relations with Cuba in regard to the
economy and trade, and that Sino-Cuban trade has always occupied a
major position in trade between China and Latin American and the
Caribbean regions.
</P>
<P>
China hopes that the bilateral trade will continue to develop
on the basis of equality and mutual benefit, Wu added.
</P>
<P>
Cabrisas noted that Cuba is ready to enhance economic and trade
cooperation with China, in a hope that this meeting will play a
positive role in the development of bilateral economic relations
and trade.
</P>
<P>
Cabrisas arrived here as Wu's guest.  
</P>
