<HEADLINE> Indian Government Reshuffled </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
S. Venugopalachari will relinquish his post at the Power
Ministry to become minister of state for agriculture.
</P>
<P>
Natarajan, a first-time entrant to the government, will also be
responsible for parliamentary affairs.
</P>
<P>
Yoginder K. Alagh, minister of state with independent charge in
the ministries of planning and program implementation and science
and technology, will give up his former portfolio and take charge
of the Power Ministry.
</P>
<P>
With Monday's reshuffle, the prime minister has relinquished
the charge of the ministries of power, urban affairs and
employment, and petroleum and natural gas. He will now
additionally hold the offices of family welfare, planning and
program implementation.
</P>
<P>
Gujral will also continue to be in charge of atomic energy,
personnel, public grievances and pension as well as electronics,
Jammu and Kashmir affairs, ocean development and space.  
</P>
