<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Xu Fu Story Still Hot for Japanese </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NINGBO, June 10 (Xinhua) -- A group of Japanese in May
investigated a site said to be the port from which an ancient
Chinese Taoist began his journey to Japan 2,000 years ago.
</P>
<P>
Members of the group belong to a society that studies Xu Fu,
who was sent by emperor Qinshihuang, the first man to unite China,
to seek longevity methods in the Pacific Ocean. But Xu finally
arrived on an island which was part of Japan.
</P>
<P>
Xu has been a hero in Japan for thousands of years as he took
with him advanced Chinese culture. Modern study shows that it was
Xu who helped Japan move into a mature agricultural society.
</P>
<P>
Xu's story becomes hot again this year when China and Japan are
celebrating the 20th anniversary of the normalization of relations
between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
But there is a mystery as where was the actual port at which Xu
and his 3,000 followers aboard the ships.
</P>
<P>
The Japanese visitors believed that the historical site was
located in Cixi city in Zhejiang province. The finding was first
made by a Chinese geologist who is also a Xu Fu expert. However,
it is still being debated. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970610.0147 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese NPC Chairman Meets Macedonian President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Qiao Shi, chairman of the Standing Committee of the Chinese
National People's Congress (NPC), made the remarks at a meeting
with President Gligorov in the Great Hall of the People here today.
</P>
<P>
Qiao welcomed Gligorov on behalf of the NPC and himself. He
said China and Macedonia are friendly countries and the two
peoples have a traditional friendship. He said he was deeply
impressed by the kindly sentiments of the Macedonians towards the
Chinese during his visit to Macedonia.
</P>
<P>
In the period since Macedonia obtained its independence in
1991, there has been new progress in Sino-Macedonian cordial and
cooperative relations, he said.
</P>
<P>
China respects the choices of the Macedonian people, attaches
importance to the bilateral relations, and wishes to expand and
develop the friendly exchanges and mutually beneficial cooperation
in political, economic, scientific and technological and cultural
fields, Qiao said. This should be carried out in line with the
principles of mutual respect, equality and mutual benefit and
non-interference in each other's internal affairs, he added.
</P>
<P>
President Gligorov said the long-term ties of friendship
between Macedonia and China are illustrated by the lack of
questions and obstacles between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Macedonia held that the road of development China has chosen
conforms entirely to China's conditions, and the Macedonian people
are concerned about its economic development and the building up
of its legal system while appreciating China's economic
achievements, he said.
</P>
<P>
Macedonia is interested in developing its friendly and
cooperative relations with China, including economic relations and
trade, President Gligorov emphasized.
</P>
<P>
Qiao said China's NPC is attentive to its relations with the
Assembly of Macedonia, and the ties constitute an important part
of the Sino-Macedonian relations as a whole.
</P>
<P>
The increase of the exchanges between the two parliaments will
be conducive to the deepening of bilateral friendship between the
two peoples and help to promote the sustained, steady and
all-round cooperation, Qiao noted.
</P>
<P>
He also promised that the NPC will work jointly with the
Macedonian Assembly, through various forms of exchange and
cooperation, to help push ahead bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
Qiao briefed the Macedonian president on China's economic
development targets and the NPC's work. He also asked the
President to convey his regards to President Tito Petkovski of the
Assembly of Macedonia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
