<HEADLINE> China, Macedonia Hold Similar Political Views: President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 10 (Xinhua) -- The President of Macedonia, Kiro
Gligorov, said here today that Sino-Macedonian relationship is
a model of bilateral relations for the world.
</P>
<P>
Though the two countries are geographically far apart, they
share similar political views, he said here this morning during a
lecture at the Chinese Academy of Social Sciences (CASS).
</P>
<P>
He expressed his satisfaction with the continuing progress and
deepening of the traditional friendly relations between the two
countries and their peoples.
</P>
<P>
China is among the first countries that recognized the
independence of the former Republic of Yugoslavia in 1993.
</P>
<P>
President Gligorov said that Macedonia highly respects China's
status and role in the international community. It also
appreciates China's understanding and supports it in the United
Nations, he said.
</P>
<P>
He held that this visit, which brought with him to China a
number of Macedonia business people, and the exchange of visits
between the business circles of the two countries will help
promote bilateral economic and trade cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Macedonia is delighted to see the success of China's reform and
opening up drive, he said, adding that he wishes the country even
greater progress in the future.
</P>
<P>
More than 300 people attended the lecture. In the audience were
Zhang Baoqing, chairman of the Chinese Government Reception
Committee and vice-minister of the State Education Commission,
Wang Renzhi, vice-president of the CASS, Zlatka Popovska, deputy
prime minister of Macedonia, Slobodan Unkovski, minister of
culture of Macedonia, and Dushan Petreski, president of the
Federation of Economy of Macedonia.  
</P>
</TEXT>
