<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Consultancy Services Developing Fast in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 10 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese capital city of
Beijing is enjoying a boom in consultancy services, with the
consultancy companies amounting to 4,758, involving a 14,000
workers.
</P>
<P>
These consultancy companies offer advisory services on economy,
technology, engineering, administration, laws, accounting and
auditing, the local source said.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that the city organized 540,000 consultancy
projects last year, with turnover topping 6.268 billion yuan,
comprising a major part in the city's economic development.
</P>
<P>
Scientific and technological consultancy service, in
particular, is growing fast, which gained 7 billion yuan over the
past five years.
</P>
<P>
The local source said that the city's China Onshore Oil
Engineering Consultancy Company (COOECC) has offered feasibility
studies and advisory appraisals for nearly 100 large and
medium-sized petroleum construction projects, saving a total of
2.8 billion yuan for the construction units. 
</P>
</TEXT>
