<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hong Kong's Return Historically Significant: Peruvian </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LIMA, June 10 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong's return to China on
July 1 this year is of historical significance of the mankind,
Peruvian Congress President Victor Joyway Rojas said here.
</P>
<P>
The return of Hong Kong enables China to resume the exercise of
sovereignty over Hong Kong, which has been part of China's
territory in history and by law, Rojas said recently in an
interview with Chinese reporters.
</P>
<P>
The return also puts an end to colonist rule in the world, he said.
</P>
<P>
In accordance with the principle of "one country, two systems,"
China keeps the economic system in Hong Kong unchanged, the top
legislator noted, and ensures that Hong Kong will enjoy extensive
autonomy in economy and culture after the return. Thus it can be
expected that the economy and culture of Hong Kong will continue
its normal development in the future, he added.
</P>
<P>
Rojas said that Peru and the People's Republic of China have
enjoyed good relations in economy and trade, finance, culture and
international cooperation, and on international issues of common
concern.
</P>
<P>
"These bilateral relations are in their best period, and we are
willing to continue strengthening them," he said.
</P>
<P>
Rojas, an ethnic Chinese born in Peru, said that as a Chinese
descendent and a friend of the Chinese people, he is especially
concerned with the development of China and happy over Hong Kong's
return. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
