<HEADLINE> German Inflation Rate Up in May </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, June 10 (Xinhua) -- Germany's inflation rate in May rose
to 1.6 percent on an annual basis, compared with 1.4 percent in
April, the Wiesbaden-based Federal Statistics Office said today.
</P>
<P>
The office said that the inflation rate in May on an annual
basis in eastern Germany was 1.8 percent and that in western
Germany was 1.5 percent.
</P>
<P>
The May figure showed a 0.4 percent monthly increase over
April. 
