<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Pipeline Connecting Tarim, Turpan-Hami Oilfields Completed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
URUMQI, June 10 (Xinhua) -- A 482-km pipeline linking Tarim and
Turpan-Hami oilfields of the Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region has
been finished and will become operational late this month.
</P>
<P>
The pipeline starts from Korla, the production base of the
Tarim Oilfield, in the west and reaches (Shanshan) Piqan, the
production center of the Turpan-Hami Oilfield, and is eventually
connected with the Lanzhou-Urumqi Railway Line.
</P>
<P>
It has a caliber of 610 mm and a designed annual capacity of
transporting five million to ten million tons of crude oil. The
whole project cost 2.2 billion yuan and began construction in
November 1995.
</P>
<P>
The oil pipeline is an auxiliary project for oil development in
Xinjiang's southern and eastern areas where more than a score of
oil and gas fields have been discovered in the past eight years.
</P>
<P>
Petroleum production facilities, with an annual capacity of
seven million tons, have been completed in a group of oilfields in
the above-mentioned two areas. Tarim, and Turpan-Hami basins
produced six million tons of crude oil and gas last year.
</P>
<P>
An official in charge of the project said that they have used
the world's most advanced technology of the 1990s, and the best
materials and equipment so that the pipeline may operate safely
for a longer time. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
