<HEADLINE> Indian Government Reshuffled </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
According to a communique issued by the Presidential Palace
late Monday night, Janeshwar Mishra was shifted from water
resources to petroleum and natural gas, M. Arunachalam from labor
to chemicals and fertilizers and Saleem Shervani from health and
family welfare to external affairs as a minister of state.
</P>
<P>
Gujral also appointed Kamla Sinha minister of state for
external affairs under his overall charge of the ministry.
</P>
<P>
Renuka Chowdhary will replace Shervani as the minister of state
for health and family welfare.
</P>
<P>
Contrary to media speculation, C. M. Ibrahim, minister of civil
aviation, retained his post. However, Jayanti Natarajan has been
appointed the minister of state in his high profile ministry.
</P>
<P>
M.P. Veerendra Kumar, minister of state for finance, has been
given independent charge of the Labor Ministry. He will also
continue to temporarily have the additional charge of the Ministry
of Urban Affairs and Employment until U. Venkateshwarlu, who is
undergoing medical treatment, assumes charge.
</P>
<P>
Ratnamala Savanoor has been given the post of minister of state
for planning and program implementation.
</P>
<P>
Chaturanan Mishra, minister for agriculture, will give up his
additional charge of food and consumer affairs which has gone to
Raghuvansh Prasad Singh with independent charge.
</P>
<P>
Mishra will also take charge of the Department of Animal
Husbandry and Dairying in the Ministry of Agriculture.
</P>
</TEXT>
