<DOCNO> XIE19970610.0172 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Southwest China's Yunnan Closes 1,575 Polluters </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, June 10 (Xinhua) -- Southwest China's Yunnan province
has closed 1,575 factories with serious pollution problems --
nearly 81 percent of those ordered to be shut down by the state.
</P>
<P>
The province's environmental report said that Yunnan has 1,951
polluters that should be closed. These factories mainly use
backward production methods and their discharge of pollutants is
far above the country's standards.
</P>
<P>
They have seriously polluted water and soil, and endangered
people's lives, officials said.
</P>
<P>
With the rapid development of the province's industries and
cities, the pollution problems have also become more
serious. Dianchi Lake has become the most polluted lake in the
country.
</P>
<P>
The provincial government has decided to spend nearly 1.5
percent of its gross natioanl product every year on
pollution control, and to spent a total of 3.5 billion yuan (about
437 million US dollars) during the 1996-2000 period.
</P>
<P>
The province spent 590 million yuan on environmental protection
last year, or about 0.4 percent of its GNP.  
</P>
</TEXT>
