<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Beijing-Xiamen Express Train Service to Be Started </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XIAMEN, June 10 (Xinhua) -- Express train service from Beijing
to Xiamen, a port city in east China's Fujian Province, will be
started in early 1998 during traditional Spring Festival season.
</P>
<P>
There is currently no through-train service from Beijing to
Xiamen or vice versa, and people travelling to both cities have to
change trains in order to reach their destinations.
</P>
<P>
Before this new route opens, express train service from Beijing
to Xiamen will be available July 1 through August 31, both to gain
experience for the express train service and to lighten the
summertime passenger overload caused mainly by college students
going home for summer holiday, according to local sources.
</P>
<P>
The first train service leaves from the Beijing Railway Station
at 00:46 hours of July 1, arrives at the Jinan Railway Station in
Shandong Province at 8:29 AM the next morning and reaches the
final stop of Xiamen, 39 hours and 26 minutes later.
</P>
<P>
The entire trip covers a distance of 2,849 km.  
</P>
</TEXT>
