<HEADLINE> Chinese City Commends Overseas-Funded Enterprises </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, June 10 (Xinhua) -- Over 100 foreign and Taiwan-funded
enterprises were recently commended by the Tianjin municipal
government for their outstanding business performances.
</P>
<P>
Among the 137 firms cited are the U.S.'s Motorola, Otis,
Japan's Honda, France's Merlin Gerin, and a Taiwanese fast food
business.
</P>
<P>
They now rank among China's leading enterprises. Motorola alone
made 350 million US dollars in profit in China last year, and the
figure is expected to exceed 500 million US dollars this year.
</P>
<P>
"Overseas-financed enterprises have become one of the major
driving forces in promoting Tianjin's economic growth. They have
contributed greatly to the improved urban infrastructure and the
double-digit increase over the past four years," said Tianjin
Mayor Zhang Lichang.
</P>
<P>
Tianjin had approved 10,800 overseas-funded ventures by the end
of April, with total contractual investment worth 16.8 billion US
dollars.
</P>
<P>
Overseas enterprises produced nearly half the city's industrial
output last year, making up 70 percent of the total profits and 34
percent of the taxes. And they account for more than half of the
city's total exports.
</P>
<P>
The enterprises crrently employ 320,000 workers. 
</P>
