<HEADLINE> China Opens Container Ocean Shipping Route </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, June 10 (Xinhua) -- Starting from Yingkou, in
northeast China's Liaoning Province, a container ocean shipping
route has opened in the country.
</P>
<P>
The itinerary begins at Yingkou's Bayuquan New Port, goes via
Shanghai, Huangpu, Shekou, and reaches Xiamen; and then returns to
Shanghai, via Qingdao, and arrives at Bayuquan.
</P>
<P>
There are three voyages on the route every month, reaching
Bayuquan port on the 5th, 15th, and 25th of a month, and starting
another voyage the next day.
</P>
<P>
For a long time, the country's coastal areas had no domestic
container shipping services. The new route, opened by the China
Ocean Shipping (Group) Company, has linked all major sea ports in
north and south China, as well as a number of inland cities.
</P>
<P>
Port authorities say that the effort will speed up the
circulation of materials between the northern and southern parts
of the country, and promote economic expansion of northeast China.
</P>
<P>
Bayuquan is a new port in Yingkou. Work on the port was
completed by 1984. The port handled nearly 15 million tons of
cargo last year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
