<HEADLINE> Tamil Rebels Attack Government Troops' Position </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, June 10 (Xinhua) -- Tamil rebels launched a massive
attack against government military positions north of Vavuniya in
Northern Province of Sri Lanka this morning, causing heavy
casualties to both sides, according to informed sources here.
</P>
<P>
The sources said artillery shells were fired from both sides
and rebels of the Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam (LTTE)
penetrated the government defense lines and directed artillery
fire toward the government military complex in Vavuniya.
</P>
<P>
Sri Lanka's Air Force fighter planes engaged LTTE gun positions
and the situation was under control there, the sources added.
</P>
<P>
