Kuwait Airways Corporation (KAC) started a strike this morning
which is expected to last 24 hours to demand pay rise.
</P>
<P>
A source at the Kuwait International Airport said all the
flights of Kuwait Airways would be canceled today because of the
strike.
</P>
<P>
An emergency meeting for the general assembly of the Kuwait
Aircraft Engineers and Pilots Association unanimously decided
Monday to observe a 24-hour strike, the source said.
</P>
<P>
They were demanding pay rise and improvement in work
conditions. The decision was made after Kuwaiti government and
KAC abruptly withdrew an offer relating to their demand that
was agreed and accepted by the pilots a few day ago.
</P>
<P>
In a strike statement, the association declared that
beginning from Wednesday June 11, all outgoing KAC flights
will be delayed for one hour apart from a 24-hour strike
every Tuesday before their demands are met.
</P>
<P>
It also said the association would meet again on June 18
to decide on the future course of action if KAC insists on
rejecting their legitimate demands.
</P>
<P>
This decision will not apply on incoming flights, the
statement said.
</P>
<P>
KAC's aircrafts fly to more than 30 destinations around the
world. 
