<HEADLINE> Beijing Urges to Recycle Fast Food Containers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 10 (Xinhua) -- The capital city of China has
urged all units or individuals who manufacture or sell plastic
food containers to recycle their products or face possibile
shut-down.
</P>
<P>
The move, which has been in effect since June 1, is part of an
effort to wipe out the city's "white pollution" caused by the
widespread use of the plastic products, said Ye Hanmin, deputy
director of the city's environmental protection bureau.
</P>
<P>
The regulation was jointly issued by the city's Environmental
Protection Bureau and the municipal Industrial and Commercial
Administration.
</P>
<P>
It requires all manufacturers or sellers of plastic fast food
containers to be registered and get permission to use the prodcut
from the two bureaus, and says their businesses could face a
forced closure if found acting against the rules.
</P>
<P>
Beijing's eight suburban areas yearly use more than 23,000 tons
of plastic products, which have posed as problems for the
environment. Fast food containers can be recycled more easily than
other plastic products.  
</P>
</TEXT>
