<DOCNO> XIE19970610.0206 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> India's Textile Exports Increase </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, June 10 (Xinhua) -- India's textile sector, which
accounts for more than one-third of the country's exports, has
managed to resist the current export slowdown much better than
other sectors, the Hindustan Times reported today.
</P>
<P>
During the month of April, textile exports recorded a
5.5-percent growth in U.S. dollar terms while the country's
overall exports declined by 10 percent, according to data released
by the Textile Ministry.
</P>
<P>
Total exports from the textile sector during April amounted to
975.74 million U.S. dollars as against 924.54 million dollars a
year earlier.
</P>
<P>
The main push to textile exports has come from cotton yarn
whose exports soared by 34.6 percent and wool and woolens, 24.8
percent.
</P>
<P>
Export of man-made textiles increased by 9.7 percent to 80.66
million dollars.
</P>
<P>
However, export of ready-made garments declined by 14 percent
in the month, a dramatic drop as such garments account for 38.9
percent of all exports from the textile sector.
</P>
<P>
The export target for the textile sector has been set at 13.3
billion dollars for the current fiscal year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
