<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 10 Million Fake Dollars Seized in Pakistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, June 10 (Xinhua) -- The Anti-Narcotics Force (ANF)
of Pakistan has seized a total of 10 million U.S. dollars in fake
notes in a dramatic swoop on a printing press in Lahore at the
weekend.
</P>
<P>
The raid was conducted on Friday but the details were released
on Monday by Ejaz Hussain Shah, the ANF's regional director, at a
press briefing in Lahore, capital of Pakistan's eastern Punjab
Province.
</P>
<P>
He said the ANF had received a tip-off sometime back that the
fake notes were being used to pay for narcotics.
</P>
<P>
He said the raid led to the discovery of this huge amount which
was hidden in various text books and took the ANF almost two days
to count.
</P>
<P>
The haul was perhaps by far the biggest of its kind in the
recent past, said Shah.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
