<HEADLINE> Laid-Off Female Workers Hired As Taxi Drivers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, June 10 (Xinhua) -- More than 500 laid-off women
workers have been hired as taxi drivers in Shijiazhuang, the
capital city of north China's Hebei Province.
</P>
<P>
"I like my new job very much," said Wang Dongmei, a laid-off
worker who took driving lessons and has been re-employed as a taxi
driver for the Hongrui Taxi Corporation in Shijiazhuang.
</P>
<P>
The taxi company has given work to 35 laid-off women workers,
whose total number in the city is more than 500.
</P>
<P>
"Although the work is hard, my income has risen a lot," Wang
said. "I would like to buy a car when I have enough money, it is
really a dream I could hardly imagine in the past." 
</P>
</TEXT>
