<HEADLINE> Former World Champion Fined for Damaging Police Car </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, June 10 (Xinhua) -- Former triple world boxing
champion Jeff Fenech was fined 360 Australian dollars (284
U.S. dollars), admitting Tuesday damaging a police car.
</P>
<P>
However, no conviction was recorded and Fenech, 33, was quoted
as saying that he was considering pursuing possible charges of
wrongful arrest and assault against police, a report from Gold
Cosast said,
</P>
<P>
The charges relate to Fenech's arrest in Surfers Paradise, on
Queensland's Gold Coast, in the early hours of February 16.
</P>
<P>
In Southport Magistrates Court Tuesday a further charge of
obscene language during arrest was amended to insulting words to a
police officer.
</P>
<P>
The court heard the incident was triggered by an alleged
domestic dispute at a nightclub on February 15.
</P>
<P>
Police attended the scene but Fenech's wife denied any
wrong-doing by her husband and the officers left.
</P>
<P>
They departed the nightclub by the back entrance to escape
autograph hunters but police were called again after another
complaint.
</P>
<P>
Up to eight officers arrived and arrested Fenech who allegedly
swore at them. The wilful damage charge related to Fenech kicking
a police vehicle at the police watchhouse.
</P>
<P>
Fenech told journalists he kicked the police car through
frustration.
nnnn
</P>
