<HEADLINE> Chinese Insurance Company Cooperating With Swiss Giant </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Tai Kang Insurance, a nationwide life insurance company that
was founded last August, expects to collect about 400 million yuan
(48 million US Dollars) in life insurance premiums this year.
</P>
<P>
The company is expected to set up four branch companies in
major Chinese economic cities this year, according to Tai Kang
officials.
</P>
<P>
John Coomber, a member of the Executive Board of Swiss
Reinsurance, said that he has confidence in China's economic
growth and that of the insurance business.
</P>
<P>
Swiss Reinsurance has long been involved in China's reinsurance
industry, and now has two representative offices in China.
</P>
<P>
Chen Dongsheng, general manager of Tai Kang Insurance, noted,
"We think that cooperating with the 134-year-old Swiss Reinsurance
Company is a turning point which will allow our company to seek
development in the world insurance market."
</P>
<P>
China has five big insurers: PICC Life, China Ping An Insurance
Co. Ltd., the Pacific Insurance Co. Ltd., New China Insurance
Co. Ltd., and Tai Kang Insurance.
</P>
<P>
It is estimated that China's life insurance companies will take
in more than 100 billion yuan (12 billion US Dollars) in premiums
by the year 2000. 
</P>
</TEXT>
