<HEADLINE> Luxury Car Sales Decline in Thailand </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, June 10 (Xinhua) -- Sales of Mercedes-Benz cars are
slowing down in Thailand due to the economic downturn in the
country, according to the local press today.
</P>
<P>
Benz Thonglor, a leading Thai Mercedes dealer, said that only
7,000 Mercedes cars were sold in 1996 in Thailand, sharply down
from the figure of 13,000 in 1995.
</P>
<P>
Dealers are being stuck with the overstock as they misjudged
the market, said Wasant Popimpanont, managing director of Benz
Thonglor.
</P>
<P>
Wasant said that his company sold 1,958 Mercedes cars during
the first four months this year, 38 percent lower than the 3,151
units it sold in the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
Recognizing the prices of Mercedes cars on the Thai market are
slightly expensive compared with other German cars, Wasant said
that Mercedes dealers are launching an interest-free payment
marketing campaign to attract customers who want to buy the cars
with installments.  
</P>
</TEXT>
