<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Hopes to See Enhanced Environmental Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TORONTO, June 9 (Xinhua) -- China puts great emphasis on the
protection of environment and hopes to see enhanced cooperation with
Canada and other countries, a senior Chinese official said here today.
</P>
<P>
Xie Zhenhua, administrator of China's National Environmental
Protection Agency (NEPA), made the remarks at a function organized by
Canada-China Business Council here.
</P>
<P>
China has always attached great importance to environmental
protection, and made it one of the nation's basic policies in
early 1980s, Xie said.
</P>
<P>
This policy has ensured that China's environment has not
deteriorated rapidly while its economy forged ahead.
</P>
<P>
Despite all this, the Chinese government knows too well that the
country faces a serious environmental protection task, said Xie, who
is here to participate in the three-day APEC Environment Ministerial
Meeting.
</P>
<P>
As China is moving toward industrialization and urbanization, it
has witnessed more and more pollution and increased destruction of
ecosystems, which in some cases has imposed threats to human lives.
</P>
<P>
To tackle this problem, China has adopted a series of legal and
administrative measures to enhance the environmental protection. And
it plans to inject some 450 billion Renminbi yuan into environmental
protection in the 1996-2000 period, Xie said.
</P>
<P>
China, while relying mainly on its own to protect the environment,
also needs the financial and technical support from the international
community and other countries.
</P>
<P>
"We hope to enhance environmental protection cooperation with
Canada, and the rest of the world as well," Xie said.
</P>
<P>
Xie noted that in recent years, China and Canada have conducted
fruitful cooperation in the management of pollution in China's Huaihe
River and Haihe River. They have also done a good job in the
prevention of overall environmental protection in Sichuan, Shandong
and other provinces.
</P>
<P>
"There is great potential for China and Canada to further enhance
their cooperation in this regard," he added.
</P>
<P>
Canada has an edge in environmental protection technology and
capital, while China boasts the relatively good basis of environmental
management and huge market. There exists great complementality between
the two countries, he said.
</P>
<P>
He expressed the hope that more Canadian entrepreneurs would go and
invest in China's environmental protection sector. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
