<HEADLINE> Banana Bunch, Believed to be World's Largest, Picked in Cuba </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAVANA, June 9 (Xinhua) -- A bunch of bananas containing 17
clusters, measuring 160 centimeters long and weighing 97 kilograms
has been cut in the eastern Cuban province of Guantanamo.
</P>
<P>
The harvest of a single banana bunch, reported by the
Trabajadores weekly published here today, was expected to make an
entry into the Guinness Book of World Records.
</P>
<P>
The bunch, of a variety locally known as the Fhia-01, exceeded
the previous record of 77 or 78 kilograms.
</P>
<P>
William Napoles, head of the plantation where the bunch was
grown, said each banana tree was fertilized three times with
potassium and urea, and given 75 liters of water each day.
</P>
<P>
Talking about his plantation, Napoles was quoted as saying that
there are several bunches of bananas containing up to 19 clusters,
therefore newer records are likely. 
</P>
</TEXT>
