<HEADLINE> U.S. Ambassador Justifies Resumption of Arms Sales </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
QUITO, June 9 (Xinhua) -- Leslie Alexander, the U.S. ambassador
to Ecuador, has justified the decision by the U.S. government to
lift its 20-year ban on arms sales to Latin America.
</P>
<P>
Alexander said the prohibition, announced by the then
U.S. President Jimy Carter, had not halted the arms race in Latin
America "since several countries acquired arms from Russia and the
arms are not very different from ours," the media today quoted him
as saying.
</P>
<P>
He said that following this new decision, Latin American
countries will be able to purchase arms from the United States,
just as other countries in Europe and Asia are now able to, the
reports said.
</P>
<P>
The arms available to Latin American countries from the United
States would not be very different with the ones they own now, he
added. Endiem

