<DOCNO> XIE19970610.0227 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Man With Transplanted Heart Dies 13 Years After Surgery </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PRAGUE, June 9 (Xinhua) -- A Czech man living with a heart
transplanted into his chest 13 years ago died last Saturday, said
a report in the newspaper Pravo published today.
</P>
<P>
Josef Divina, believed to have carried a transplanted heart for
the longest time in the world's medical history, was 57.
</P>
<P>
Once suffering a life-threatening heart condition, Divina
underwent a surgical procedure at a hospital here on January 31,
1984, to receive a donated human heart.
</P>
<P>
The surgery proved a success. And he was able to lead a normal
life, traveled abroad three times, and served as the top quality
supervisor at a factory.
</P>
<P>
However, while family members and friends were reportedly
gathering on June 3 to mark another anniversary of his birthday,
Divina fainted and collapsed.
</P>
<P>
His death three days later at a hospital was attributed by
doctors to cerebral hemorrhage, a condition apparently unrelated
to the heart transplant. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
