<HEADLINE> Harmoko Likely to Be Indonesia's Next House Speaker </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, June 10 (Xinhua) -- Outgoing Information Minister
Harmoko will most likely become Indonesia's next chairman of the
House of Representatives (DPR) and People's Consultative Assembly
(MPR), a senior official said.
</P>
<P>
"There are strong indications to believe Harmoko will become
DPR/MPR chairman," Supreme Advisory Council (DPA) Chairman Sudomo
said here Monday.
</P>
<P>
Harmoko is currently chairman of the ruling Golkar party, the
virtual winner of the recent general election in the country.
</P>
<P>
President Soeharto last Friday appointed Harmoko as state
minister for special affairs while Army Chief of Staff General
Hartono will replace him as minister of information.
</P>
<P>
Sudomo said he believed the replacement of Harmoko as
information minister had been planned before. He said he did not
believe the change was linked with the next vice president.
</P>
<P>
MPR will elect president and vice president in March next year.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Harmoko said here Monday that he would stay in
cabinet as state minister of special affairs until September 30,
before taking a seat in the House.
</P>
<P>
"Our administrative system does not allow a legislator to serve
concurrently in a government position, so I will leave the cabinet
before October," he said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
