<HEADLINE> Volcanic Eruption Kills 2 in Indonesia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, June 10 (Xinhua) -- Indonesian rescuers have found two
people dead and one seriously injured from Sunday's eruption of
Mount Karangetang on the Island of Siau in North Sulawesi, Antara
news agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
The three victims were watching the lava pouring out of the
erupting crater, when they were hit by clouds of hot steam which
raged down the banks of the Keting river.
</P>
<P>
The volcano has been having minor eruptions since April 19,
causing a constant flow of lava to pour out of the crater.
</P>
<P>
Volcanic hot steam clouds can reach temperature of 600 degrees
Celsius destroying almost anything in their path.
</P>
<P>
Six people in the village of Dame near Mount Karangetang died
in a similar accident in 1992, reports said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
