<HEADLINE> Development of Kathmandu Valley Discussed in Nepal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, June 10 (Xinhua) -- The Nepali government held a
discussion program Monday on phase-wise development of the
Kathmandu Valley, press reports here said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Participants from different government bodies held extensive
discussions on such problems as safe drinking water, solid waste,
pollution, transport and construction work that beset the
Kathmandu Valley.
</P>
<P>
Deputy Prime Minister and Home Minister Bamdev Gautam, who
chaired the discussion program at his office, demanded that
immediate steps be taken towards formulating a master plan for
long-term solution to the problems and the integrated development
of the valley.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that the development of the valley should be
divided into long-term, short-term and immediate phases.
</P>
<P>
A decision was made to constitute a task force, comprising
officials from various government departments, to identify work to
be done immediately and present a report within a week.  
