<HEADLINE> Thai Exports to China Drop in First Quarter </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, June 10 (Xinhua) -- Thailand's exports to China in the
first quarter this year posted 10.97 billion baht (about 438.8
million U.S. dollars), down 14 percent compared with the same
period of last year.
</P>
<P>
Thailand's trade deficit with China in the first three months
of this year recorded 3.82 billion baht (152.8 million dollars),
with China's exports to Thailand rising 22 percent to 14.79
billion baht (591.6 million dollars), according to statistics from
the Thai Commerce Ministry.
</P>
<P>
Thailand mainly exported rubber, computers, chemicals, rice,
fish and fabrics to China, while importing machinery and parts,
computers, industrial machinery and electrical appliances from
China during the period.  
