<HEADLINE> Process for Nepal's WTO Entry Underway </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, June 10 (Xinhua) -- The Nepali government is close
to finalize a draft memorandum on foreign trade regime seeking the
country's accession to the World Trade Organization (WTO),
official sources here said today.
</P>
<P>
The government formed a special committee comprising
high-ranking officials last year to speed up the process to seek
WTO membership, according to an official of the Commerce Ministry.
</P>
<P>
The draft memorandum will be sent to the WTO working party in
Geneva for study, he said.
</P>
<P>
Nepal's request for WTO membership would be approved by the
organization's biannual ministerial conference if the working
party recommends so after studying the draft memorandum.
</P>
<P>
Nepal at present holds an observer status at the World Trade
Organization.
</P>
<P>
A workshop on Nepal's entry to the WTO was held here over the
weekend jointly by the Commerce Ministry and the United Nations
Development Program (UNDP), which has been supporting Nepal's
efforts to obtain WTO membership.
</P>
<P>
Trade experts here said that the open and liberal economic
policies adopted in the early 1990s by the government and relevant
legal infrastructure are adequate for Nepal to become a full WTO
member.
</P>
<P>
Experts at the seminar urged the government to adjust the
country's economy to address the lingering problems like low
export base, export volatility and trade payment imbalances.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
