<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New Bulgaria's Army's Chief to Be Appointed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SOFIA, June 9 (Xinhua) -- The Bulgarian government Monday
decided to suggest that President Petar Stoyanov appoint Air Force
Commander M. Mikhov as new chief of general staff of the Bulgarian
Army, the country's news agency Bulnet reported.
</P>
<P>
Mikhov is expected to replace current Chief of General Staff
Tsvetan Totomirov, who will be named as the president's national
security secretary, the report said.
</P>
<P>
Defense Minister Georgi Ananiev told reporters that Stoyanov
and Prime Minister Ivan Kostov had discussed the government's
suggestion.
</P>
<P>
He also suggested that the generals of all forces act in turn
as the chief of general staff, a post usually held by a
high-ranking army officer. 
</P>
