<HEADLINE> China to Build First CT Scanner Production Base </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, June 10 (Xinhua) -- The Alpa Software Group under
Northeast China University has just gained approval from the state
to build China's first CT scanner production base with designed
capacity of 100 a year.
</P>
<P>
Approved by the State Pharmaceutical Administration, the group
is to produce its newly developed CT-C2000 scanners, which detect
tumors in the human body.
</P>
<P>
The company is also China's first producer of CT scanner for
whole body check-ups which was developed in 1994.
</P>
<P>
The latest CT-C2000 scanner is believed to be up to the world's
standard technologically, but only is half of the price
compared with similar models on the world market.
</P>
<P>
It is also equipped with a Chinese character display
system. The group can conduct remote-control maintenance of their
scanners among its customers all over the country with the help of
their computer network.
</P>
<P>
China has been relying on imported CT scanners in the past
years. Since the 1980s, the country has spent over one billion US
dollar to buy the CT scanners.
</P>
<P>
The production base is expected to become operational this fall.
 
</P>
</TEXT>
