<HEADLINE> Ukraine Expects to Buy Oil From Iran </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, June 9 (Xinhua) -- Ukraine expected to buy oil from
Iran, Ukrainian Foreign Minister Gennady Udovenko said Monday
at a meeting with his Iranian counterpart Ali Akbar Velayati.
</P>
<P>
Velayati, who paid a one-day visit to Kiev, said Iran has no
limits or misgivings in providing oil for Ukraine.
</P>
<P>
The most important part of the oil cooperation is a three-way
deal among Iran, Ukraine and Turkmenistan, Velayati added.
</P>
<P>
Under the deal to be signed on June 27, Ukraine will pay part
of its multi-million U.S. dollars gas debt to Turkmenistan by
supplying 52 million dollars worth of railroad cars and wheels to
Iran. In turn, Iran would pay Turkmenistan in hard currency.
</P>
<P>
Velayati also expressed Iran's wishes to build a pipeline to
link Iran with Ukraine and to invest in the renovation of the
latter's largest oil terminal Odessa, a port in southern Ukraine.
</P>
<P>
During his stay in Kiev, Velayati also met with Ukrainian
President Leonid Kuchma. 
