<HEADLINE> Feats of Overseas Chinese Showcased </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 10 (Xinhua) -- A major exhibition is to be held in
Beijing which will focus on the economic achievements of people of
Chinese origin living all over the world, according to today's
China Daily.
</P>
<P>
The paper said that the September event, the first of its kind
in China, will include a second show dedicated to displaying art
works by women of Chinese origin.
</P>
<P>
The aim is to encourage overseas Chinese to contribute more to
the prosperity of the mainland, said Zhang Qi, director of the
China Women and Children Development Center.
</P>
<P>
More than 60 enterprises in the United States, Thailand,
Malaysia, Singapore and other countries have so far applied to
attend the show. Many joint ventures in China are also interested,
said Zhang, whose center is sponsoring the two shows.
</P>
<P>
During the four-day exhibition, meetings for technological
exchanges, product shows, trade talks and discussions with senior
officials from the Chineses Government and its financial
departments will be arranged for the exhibitors, she said. This
will be a chance to give an overview of the country's investment
policies and priorities, it will also act as a warning to avoid
random investments which do not suit the State situation.  
