<BODY>
<HEADLINE> NZ to Close Five TV Stations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WELLINGTON, June 10 (Xinhua) -- Five regional television
stations in New Zealand will soon go off the air to make way for a
youth-oriented station, local newspaper The Dominion reported
today.
</P>
<P>
The stations to be closed are located in the five major cities:
Auckland, Wellington, Christchurch, Dunedin and Hamiton. A total
of 120 people are expected to lose their jobs.
</P>
<P>
The paper quoted a TVNZ source as saying that the new-look
youth station is to be based in Auckland and comes as a
"competitive response" to the plans of the privately owned TV3 to
start a new youth channel at the end of this month.
</P>
<P>
The mayors of the Wellington region issued a statement last
night, opposing the closure. But a spokesman for Communications
Minister Maurice Williamson has said that it is up to TVNZ what it
does with its regional stations.
</P>
<P>
TVNZ is owned by the government. But there is no need to get
government approval for the move to a youth station because it
does not involve a big capital investment, the TVNZ source was
quoted as saying.  
</P>
</TEXT>
