<HEADLINE> Shanghai Sells Freezer Production line To Indonesia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 10 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai recently signed an
agreement with an Indonesian company to export a freezer
production line to Indonesia.
</P>
<P>
The new line, which was designed and manufactured by a local
research institute with the ship-building industry, is the first
of its kind to be sold in the southeast Asian country.
</P>
<P>
The Shanghai No. 704 Institute has nearly 1,000 researchers and
specializes in designing freezers of various kinds. The institute
has also manufactured a washing-machine production line for the
same foreign company.
</P>
<P>
In recent years, many military industrial firms in the country
have started making products for commercial and civil use in line
with the government's policy to develop a market economy. 
</P>
