<HEADLINE> Truck Drivers Block European Traffic </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, June 9 (Xinhua) -- Thousands of truck drivers today
blocked major traffic arteries in Germany, Poland, France, Spain
and Switzerland to demand European-wide legislation limiting
working time to 12 hours a day, said reports reaching here.
</P>
<P>
The protest caused long traffic jams at the major border
crossings between Germany and Poland, France and Spain as well as
France and Switzerland. The truck drivers only left one lane to
let passenger cars through.
</P>
<P>
The action came after European truck drivers unions called for
new European legislation. They complained that truck drivers were
often forced to ignore legal breaks and maximum time at the wheel
of 10 hours. 
</P>
