<HEADLINE> European Shares Mixed, London Ends Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, June 9 (Xinhua) -- Shares on Europe's major stock
markets mixed today, with London finishing higher and Frankfurt
and Paris ending lower.
</P>
<P>
British shares closed with solid gains as investors shrugged
off a weak gilts market and tumbling European bourses and instead
looked to Wall Street, where the Dow scaled new peaks, dealers
said. The benchmark FTSE-100 share index ended 41.7 points higher
at 4,686.7.
</P>
