start in the morning, as an upsurge in worries about monetary
union offset initial optimism about U.S. economic prospects. The
DAX index closed down 27.86 points at 3,667.43, dropping nearly 70
points from the historic intraday high of 3,734.05 points set in
pre-bourse electronic dealings.
</P>
<P>
French shares ended 1.22 percent lower, after a sudden panic
over the future of the European Economic and Monetary Union. The
CAC-40 index closed down 33.05 at 2,686.2. 
