<HEADLINE> World Bank Approves Two Credits for West Bank, Gaza </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 9 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank today announced
the approval of two credits totaling 8.8 million U.S. dollars for
Palestinian territories of West Bank and Gaza projects.
</P>
<P>
The first credit of some 5.5 million dollars equivalent is
provided to a legal development project which is aimed to assist
the Palestinian Authority in putting in place a legal framework
that would increase the efficiency of the judicial process and be
conducive to private sector development.
</P>
<P>
The other credit of 3.3 million dollars equivalent will be for
a Palestinian expatriates professional program project, which is
designed to attract Palestinian professionals abroad to help
manage departments in Palestinian Authority ministries and
agencies or to serve in senior technical positions. About 150
Palestinian professionals are expected to be recruited under the
project.
</P>
<P>
The credits will be channeled through the International
Development Association, the concessionary lending arm of the
World Bank for developing countries. 
</P>
